23/10/2006
ZAGREB, Croatia -- A survey of the 30 biggest Croatian companies by the Foundation for Economic Interests Promotion suggests that local managers are not well-acquainted with EU regulations and standards. 
According to results published in Monday's (October 23rd) edition of Vecernji list, the average score of Croatian managers as regards knowledge in this field was 3.6 points out of 10, well below the 9.5 average in EU member countries. 
Managers in Bulgaria, Romania and Turkey scored an average of 5 points. 
(Vecernji list - 23/10/06)
